<br>
I disagree.  I think that the delitorious effect of microgravity are essentially rendered moot by the inclusion of a spinning teather in the Mars direct plan. <br>
<br>
Also, while the exact physiological effect of solar flares in not known precisely, we do know enough about them to shield astronauts from danger.  This could be accomplished with only a few centimeters of water.<br>
<br>
I think NASA would be delighted to squander our money by spending several more decades to research the effects of long-term spaceflight in orbit before they venture farther.  It would mean assured funding and minimal risk, political and technological, for them.  What more could a bloated government agency want?<br>
<br>
All of the data that the ISS can gather about these subjects has allready been aquired by the Russians in one or more of their 8 space stations.<br>
<br>
I think there is no reason to postpone a mars mission at this point in time.<br>
<br>
That is not to say that Mars should be our exclusive goal either.  I am all in favor of a return to the moon, with astronomy gear this time, and missions to NEOs and main belt asteroids, as well as the outer planets.  I think we have the technology and money to pursue all of these goals and we have no excuse not to.<br>
<br>
I just think NASA's overemphasis on trivialities like microgravity research,  radiation research, human factors, etc..., are counterproductive when they crowd out real exploration.  Especialy since these are paper tigers.  I mean, who would subject themselves to long periods of microgravity when centripital acceleration is so easy to create?         <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nebobgrenville>nebobgrenville</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://my.oregonstate.edu/courses/1/NE_114_X001_F2002/uploads/homepage/_1060577_1/triga.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 272<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/3/03 2:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=773.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Our next step in space?</span><hr size=1> Radiation is very well understood, and it takes a lot more then few cm of water to stop cosmic radiation, especialy during a solar flare. The only mass resonible way to shield the crew from flares is with a small storm shelter, it would take too much mass to shield the whole ship to this level. <p>&quot;If,&quot; he wispered, &quot;if we could only pick that lock....&quot; - , THE WORLD SET FREE</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=megaloman84>Megaloman84</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(3/3/03 4:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=773.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Our next step in space?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Radiation is very well understood, and it takes a lot more then few cm of water to stop cosmic radiation, especialy during a solar flare. The only mass resonible way to shield the crew from flares is with a small storm shelter, it would take too much mass to shield the whole ship to this level.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It does take a lot more than a few cm of water to shield against cosmic rays.  Indeed it takes so much, the equivalent of of a few meters, that it would be impractical do so in a ship of any size we will be using in the near future.  However, these cosmic rays are few and far between.  The dosage from such cosmic rays should not exceed about 50 rem for a Mars expedition, according to Robert Zubrin.  This represents about a 1% statistical increase in the chance of getting a fatal cancer at some point in life.  Compair this to the 20% increase that occurs with regular smoking and weigh the risk. <br>
<br>
The charged particles that eminate from the sun during a solar flare, however, represent an immediate lethal risk to any astronaut in interstellar space when such an outburst occurs.  They can deliver thousands of rems in only a few hours to an unshielded human.  Fortunately, these have a  much lower energy than cosmic rays and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>can</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be stopped with only a few cm of water.  RZ proposes storing the expedition's food and water around a central &quot;storm shelter&quot;, which is the size of a closet and could accomodate the crew for a few hours until the flare dies down.<br>
<br>
The risk is fundamentaly understood and can be dealt with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=773.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=773.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=773.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=773.topic&index=23><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=773.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.threadControl?topicID=773.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=773.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=773.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr alig